{
  "info": {
    "name": "KOSMO SDD API",
    "description": "Colección completa del flujo SDD (Spec-Driven Development) de KOSMO.\n\n## Flujo completo\n\n0. Health — sanity check\n1. Auth PKCE S256 — Register → Authorize → Token → Refresh → Me → Logout\n2. Proyectos — Crear proyecto (nombre + descripción = input del discovery)\n3. Discovery — Generar (desde nombre/descripción del proyecto) → Obtener → Guardar\n4. Features — Generar (5 iniciales desde discovery) → Sugerir (3 nuevas) → Guardar → Listar\n5. Requisitos EARS — Generar por feature → Guardar\n\n## IDs\n\nULID con prefijo tipado: prj_ (project), feat_ (feature), usr_ (user).\nDisplay IDs: C01, C02 (number secuencial, humano).\n\n## Pre-requisitos\n\n- uv run uvicorn kosmo.infrastructure.api.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000\n- Usuario seed: uv run python -m kosmo.infrastructure.scripts.seed_dev_user",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "email", "value": "dev@kosmo.dev", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "dev-password-12345", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "access_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "refresh_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "user_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "authorization_code", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "code_verifier", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "code_challenge", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "project_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "feature_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "feature_id_alt", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0. Health",
      "description": "Verificar que el servidor responde correctamente.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Health Check",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('status = ok', function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('ok'); });"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/health", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["health"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1. Auth (PKCE S256)",
      "description": "Flujo OAuth 2.1 + PKCE completo. Las variables se auto-propagan entre requests.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1.1 Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function setVar(key, value) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value); if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) pm.environment.set(key, value); }",
                  "pm.test('201 o 409', function () { pm.expect([201, 409]).to.include(pm.response.code); });",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  setVar('user_id', body.id);",
                  "  console.log('Usuario creado:', body.id);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.log('Usuario ya existe (409) — OK');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "1.2 Authorize (PKCE S256)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function b64url(wordArray) { return CryptoJS.enc.Base64.stringify(wordArray).replace(/\\+/g, '-').replace(/\\//g, '_').replace(/=+$/g, ''); }",
                  "var verifier = b64url(CryptoJS.lib.WordArray.random(48));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('code_verifier', verifier);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('code_challenge', b64url(CryptoJS.SHA256(verifier)));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function setVar(key, value) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value); if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) pm.environment.set(key, value); }",
                  "pm.test('201 Created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "setVar('authorization_code', body.authorization_code);",
                  "console.log('Authorization code obtenido. Expira en:', body.expires_in, 's');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\",\n  \"code_challenge\": \"{{code_challenge}}\",\n  \"code_challenge_method\": \"S256\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/authorize", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "authorize"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "1.3 Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function setVar(key, value) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value); if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) pm.environment.set(key, value); }",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "setVar('access_token', body.access.token);",
                  "setVar('refresh_token', body.refresh.token);",
                  "console.log('Tokens obtenidos.');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"grant_type\": \"authorization_code\",\n  \"code\": \"{{authorization_code}}\",\n  \"code_verifier\": \"{{code_verifier}}\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/token", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "token"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "1.4 Refresh Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function setVar(key, value) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value); if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) pm.environment.set(key, value); }",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "setVar('access_token', body.access.token);",
                  "setVar('refresh_token', body.refresh.token);",
                  "console.log('Tokens rotados.');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"grant_type\": \"refresh_token\",\n  \"refresh_token\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/refresh", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "refresh"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "1.5 Me (get Principal)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function setVar(key, value) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value); if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) pm.environment.set(key, value); }",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "setVar('user_id', body.subject);",
                  "console.log('Principal:', body.subject);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "me"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "1.6 Logout",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('204 No Content', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(204); });",
                  "console.log('Sesión revocada.');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"refresh_token\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/logout", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "logout"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Proyectos",
      "description": "CRUD de proyectos. El proyecto inicia en fase 'descubrimiento'. IDs con prefijo prj_. El nombre y descripción del proyecto son el input para generar el discovery.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "2.1 Crear Proyecto",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function setVar(key, value) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value); if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) pm.environment.set(key, value); }",
                  "pm.test('201 Created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "setVar('project_id', body.id);",
                  "console.log('Proyecto:', body.id, '-', body.name);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"División de Gastos Compartidos\",\n  \"description\": \"Aplicación para grupos de amigos o roomies que permite registrar gastos compartidos, calcular balances automáticos y sugerir la forma más eficiente de liquidar deudas.\",\n  \"owner_id\": \"{{user_id}}\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "projects"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2.2 Listar Proyectos",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "var data = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('Proyectos:', data.length);",
                  "data.forEach(function(p) { console.log('  -', p.name, '| ID:', p.id); });"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects?owner_id={{user_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "projects"],
              "query": [{ "key": "owner_id", "value": "{{user_id}}" }]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2.3 Obtener Proyecto",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('Proyecto:', body.name, '| Fase:', body.current_phase);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "projects", "{{project_id}}"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Discovery (Fase 1)",
      "description": "Documento de descubrimiento generado por IA (9 secciones). El input se toma del nombre y descripción del proyecto. No requiere body. Respuesta: { document_markdown }.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "3.1 Generar Discovery (IA)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  console.log('Discovery generado (' + body.document_markdown.length + ' chars)');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/discovery/generate", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "projects", "{{project_id}}", "discovery", "generate"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3.2 Obtener Discovery",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  console.log('Discovery obtenido (' + body.document_markdown.length + ' chars)');",
                  "} else if (pm.response.code === 404) {",
                  "  console.log('[404] No hay discovery. Ejecutá 3.1.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/discovery", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "projects", "{{project_id}}", "discovery"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3.3 Guardar Discovery (edición manual)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  console.log('Discovery guardado.');",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.log('[ERROR]', pm.response.text());",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"markdown\": \"## Visión del producto\\n\\nAplicación para grupos que permite registrar gastos compartidos y calcular balances automáticos.\\n\\n## Espacio del problema\\n\\nDividir gastos en grupos genera tensiones y errores manuales. No existe una herramienta simple que automatice el balance.\\n\\n## Actores\\n\\n- **Roomie:** miembro del grupo que comparte gastos.\\n- **Administrador:** usuario que configura el grupo.\\n\\n## Propuesta de valor\\n\\n- **Para Roomie:** evita cálculos manuales.\\n- **Para Administrador:** centraliza la gestión.\\n\\n## Casos de uso\\n\\n1. **Registrar gasto:** un miembro ingresa un gasto y selecciona participantes.\\n2. **Calcular balance:** el sistema calcula cuánto debe cada persona.\\n3. **Sugerir liquidación:** el sistema propone la ruta de pagos más eficiente.\\n\\n## Capacidades principales\\n\\n- **Registro de gastos:** captura monto, concepto, pagador y participantes.\\n- **Balance automático:** calcula saldos individuales en tiempo real.\\n\\n## Reglas de negocio\\n\\n1. Un gasto debe tener al menos un pagador y un participante.\\n2. El reparto puede ser equitativo, por porcentaje o por montos fijos.\\n3. El balance se recalcula tras cada nuevo gasto.\\n4. Un grupo solo puede cerrarse con saldos en cero.\\n\\n## Atributos de calidad\\n\\n- **Precisión:** balance exacto, sin errores de redondeo.\\n- **Rapidez:** cálculo del balance en menos de 2 segundos.\\n\\n## Alcance\\n\\n*Incluido:*\\n- Registro de gastos con reparto equitativo, porcentual o fijo.\\n- Cálculo automático de balances individuales.\\n\\n*Excluido:*\\n- Integración con bancos o pasarelas de pago.\\n- Gestión de ingresos o presupuestos personales.\\n- Soporte para múltiples monedas.\\n\\n*Futuro potencial:*\\n- Sincronización con calendarios para gastos recurrentes.\\n- Exportación de balances a hojas de cálculo.\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/discovery", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "projects", "{{project_id}}", "discovery"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Features (Fase 2)",
      "description": "Características del producto. Se generan 5 iniciales desde el discovery. Se pueden sugerir 3 adicionales que no dupliquen las existentes. Todas las features son elegibles para requisitos.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "4.1 Generar Features (IA, 5 iniciales)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function setVar(key, value) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value); if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) pm.environment.set(key, value); }",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Generó features', function () { pm.expect(body.features).to.be.an('array'); pm.expect(body.total).to.eql(body.features.length); });",
                  "if (body.features && body.features.length > 0) {",
                  "  setVar('feature_id', body.features[0].id);",
                  "  if (body.features.length > 1) setVar('feature_id_alt', body.features[1].id);",
                  "}",
                  "console.log('Features generadas:', body.total);",
                  "body.features.forEach(function(f, i) { console.log('  ' + (i+1) + '.', f.display_id, f.title); });"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/features/generate", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "projects", "{{project_id}}", "features", "generate"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "4.2 Listar Features",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function setVar(key, value) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value); if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) pm.environment.set(key, value); }",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (body.features && body.features.length > 0) {",
                  "  setVar('feature_id', body.features[0].id);",
                  "}",
                  "console.log('Features:', body.total);",
                  "body.features.forEach(function(f) { console.log('  -', f.display_id, f.title, '|', f.created_at); });"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/features", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "projects", "{{project_id}}", "features"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "4.3 Sugerir Features (IA, 3 adicionales)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  console.log('Sugerencias:', body.suggestions.length);",
                  "  body.suggestions.forEach(function(s, i) { console.log('  ' + (i+1) + '.', s.display_id, s.title); });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/features/suggest", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "projects", "{{project_id}}", "features", "suggest"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "4.4 Guardar Features Seleccionadas",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "function setVar(key, value) { pm.collectionVariables.set(key, value); if (pm.environment && pm.environment.name) pm.environment.set(key, value); }",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('Features guardadas:', body.total);",
                  "body.features.forEach(function(f) { console.log('  -', f.display_id, f.title); });"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"project_id\": \"{{project_id}}\",\n  \"selected_suggestions\": [\n    {\n      \"number\": 6,\n      \"title\": \"Notificaciones de deudas\",\n      \"description\": \"Envía alertas a los miembros del grupo cuando tienen deudas pendientes o cuando reciben un pago, manteniendo a todos informados sobre el estado de sus cuentas.\",\n      \"rationale\": \"Las notificaciones mantienen a los usuarios al tanto sin necesidad de revisar manualmente la aplicación.\",\n      \"inferred_from\": [\"Casos de uso\", \"Actores\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/features", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "projects", "{{project_id}}", "features"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Requisitos EARS (Fase 3)",
      "description": "Generación de requisitos EARS por feature. Cualquier feature existente puede generar requisitos.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "5.1 Generar Requisitos EARS (IA)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  console.log('Requisitos generados para feature', body.feature_number);",
                  "  console.log('Total requisitos:', body.requirements.length);",
